# **Data Type Definition:**
# A **data type** is a classification that specifies what type of value a variable can store and what operations can be performed on it.

# | Data Type             | Definition                                                                                        | Example                         |
# | --------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------- |
# | **int**               | Used to store whole numbers without decimal points.                                               | `10`                            |
# | **float**             | Used to store numbers that contain decimal values.                                                | `3.14`                          |
# | **complex**           | Used to store numbers that have a real and imaginary part.                                        | `2 + 3j`                        |
# | **str (String)**      | Used to store text or characters inside quotes.                                                   | `"Hello"`                       |
# | **bool (Boolean)**    | Used to represent logical values **True** or **False**.                                           | `True`                          |
# | **list**              | Used to store multiple items in a single variable using square brackets and items can be changed. | `[1, 2, 3]`                     |
# | **tuple**             | Used to store multiple items in a single variable using parentheses and items cannot be changed.  | `(1, 2, 3)`                     |
# | **set**               | Used to store unique values where duplicate values are not allowed.                               | `{1, 2, 3}`                     |
# | **dict (Dictionary)** | Used to store data in **key–value pairs**.                                                        | `{"name": "Deepak", "age": 25}` |
